@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Kafka Three Node KRaft Quorum

' Why three nodes? A quorum needs a majority to make progress.
' Three nodes tolerate losing one and still have two left, which is a majority.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

rectangle "orbit-kafka (Strimzi, KRaft - no ZooKeeper)" {
  node "node 0\ncontroller + broker" as n0
  node "node 1\ncontroller + broker" as n1
  node "node 2\ncontroller + broker" as n2

  n0 <--> n1 : raft metadata
  n1 <--> n2 : raft metadata
  n0 <--> n2 : raft metadata
}

note bottom of n1 : Each node is both a controller that votes in the quorum and a broker that holds data.

note as cfg
  RF=3 and min.insync.replicas=2. Lose one node,
  lose no data, and the quorum holds with two of three.
end note

cfg .. n2

@enduml
